article.headline: Winthrop 78, High Point 67
article.story: ROCK HILL, S.C. (AP) -- Marcus Cooke scored a career-high 24 points in a 78-67 Winthrop victory over High Point on Wednesday night -- its third straight against the Panthers. The win improves the Eagles' all-time lead in the series to 13-1. The loss was the fourth in the past five games for the Panthers (14-9, 7-5 Big South). Winthrop (14-10, 8-5), which shot 59 percent in the second half, broke away from High Point in the final seven minutes of the game. With the game tied at 57-57, James Shuler scored to put the Eagles ahead for good at 59-57 with 6:21 left in the game. Torrell Martin, who had missed 10 conference games because of a knee injury, put the Eagles up 69-62 with a tip-in, layup and an 18-foot jumper over the next two minutes. The Eagles built the lead to 13 at 76-63 with just over one minute left in the contest. Jerry Echenique led High Point with 15 points, and Danny Gathings had 14 points and a game-high 12 rebounds. Martin scored 18 for Winthrop.
